template.name: Service Zabbix Proxy
template.description:
Base Zabbix proxy service monitoring template.
Version: 1.0.4 (2018-06-11) URL: https://github.com/kloczek/zabbix-templates/tree/master/Service%20Zabbix%20Proxy
Notes: * Host with this template must be monitored over proxy which will be monitored.

trigger.expression: (({Service Zabbix Proxy:logrt[/var/log/zabbix/zabbix_proxy.log,"cannot send list of active checks to \[.*\] failed: host \[.*\] not found",,].regexp(not found)})>0)
trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_proxy::hosts are failing requesting for configuration
trigger.description:
We have detected an error in the logs similar to this:
499:20131203:021029.181 Sending list of active checks to [172.16.18.193] failed: host [app001.aci100.uk3.ribob01.net] not found
This means that a host may be failing to auto-register, subsequently we will have no monitoring data for this host and manual intervention is required to get it into monitoring.

trigger.name: SVC::zabbix_proxy::No data >= 1min
trigger.description: Zabbix proxy last data received more than 1 min ago. Possible: - communication issue between zabbix server and proxy - proxy is down
